object.name: MU FP
object.tag: For includion of the priorities definition.

Interest has been expressed by the US Office of National Coordinator (ONC), CMS, CDC and many others (including international organizations) regarding the correspondence of US Meaningful Use certification criteria with related EHR System functions and conformance criteria of HL7/ISO 10781, EHR System Functional Model Release 2. This also opens the potential for EHR Systems to be certified against MU Stage 1 & 2 criteria (US realm) and related HL7/ISO 10781 criteria (international) simultaneously – without extra work by the certifier or certified entity.

The scope of this project is to develop an EHR System Meaningful Use Functional Profile, referred hereafter as MU FP, by identifying functions/criteria from HL7/ISO 10781, EHR System Functional Model Release 2, pertinent to U.S. Meaningful Use (MU) Stages 1, 2 (and 3, as it develops) and aligning the same with ONC 2014 Certification Criteria. The HL7 Meaningful Use Functional Profile (MU FP) conforms to the HL7 EHR-S FM Release 2.0 and identifies functional requirements and conformance criteria corresponding to US Meaningful Use Stage 1 and 2 certification criteria.

object.name: CPS.4.2.3#X

object.name: CP.1.1#X
object.notes: The system SHALL provide the ability to capture an indication of the patient's tobacco use and/or exposure (e.g., chewing tobacco and cigar usage; exposure of a baby to cigarette smoke in the home).
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CP.1.1#X
object.notes: The system SHALL provide the ability to capture information regarding the time period of the patient's tobacco use and/or exposure (e.g., cigarette smoker from 1992 to 1994, ten cigarettes per day, but no longer smokes; exposure of a baby to cigarette smoke in the home since birth in 2007, parents continue to smoke heavily; constant chewing tobacco usage since 1985).
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CP.1.1#X
object.notes: IF the patient's use of tobacco is unknown, THEN the system SHALL provide the ability to capture an "Unknown" indicator accordingly.
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CP.1.1#X
object.notes: IF the patient's exposure to the use of tobacco by people residing at the patient's residence is unknown, THEN the system SHALL provide the ability to capture an "Unknown" indicator.
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CPS.2.4#X
object.notes: The system SHALL provide the ability to render clinical images with associated narrative interpretations.
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CP.1.1#X
object.notes: The system SHALL provide the ability to manage family health history as structured data according to IHTSDO SNOMED CT®, as applicable.
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CP.1.1#X
object.notes: The system SHALL provide tha ability to management family health history as structured data according to HL7 Version 3 Standard for Clinical Genomics/Pedigree.
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory

object.name: CP.6.1#X
object.notes: The system SHALL provide the ability to determine and render if all of the "five rights" are correct, i.e., right patient, right medication, right dose, right route, right time, and any variance if not.
object.tag: Description: capture reason for change / institutional memory
